b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Gencraft is best suited for mobile art, social sharing, artistic effects, casual creation, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Ideogram, meanwhile, shines for logos, typography, text in images, poster design, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2022, Gencraft describes itself as \"Mobile AI art generator with unique artistic filters.\" Ideogram, established in 2023, positions itself as \"AI image generator excelling at text, logos, and typography.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Ideogram** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 4.0), more features (7 vs 3), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Gencraft is a poor choice — far from it. Gencraft excels in its own right, particularly for mobile art and social sharing.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value excellent text rendering, especially for logos, go with Ideogram. If fun artistic filters and styles matters more to you, Gencraft is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
